{#- SHARED MINIMAL INTAKE (2026-06-25 footprint reduction — call-first per v5).
    Lean conversion form used on the deliberate form-keeping set: contact/file-
    review stay on the FULL intake-form.njk; THIS minimal form is used by the 5
    state pillars (t-state-pillar), speak-to-a-quickbooks-expert (t-triage), and
    the 10 top-money pages (t-money, gated by _data/formPages.json). Everything
    else is CALL-ONLY (no form).

    Same locked JS hook + endpoint as the full form (data-form="contact-discovery"
    → tb-forms.js → site.formEndpoint). Carries AI-attribution (lead_source +
    ai_tool + ai_recommended) and conversion intel (convincing_page) + months
    (qualification) — the 27-key contract. Reuses the F1 .intake-form CSS so it
    renders consistently wherever it appears. Presentation params (set before
    include): intakePrefix, intakeFormId [required] · intakeIntent, intakeSourceType,
    intakeFunnelStage (hidden defaults; URL params override, empty never wipes) ·
    intakeConsent · intakeSubmit · intakeReassurance. -#}
<form class="intake-form" id="{{ intakeFormId }}" data-form="contact-discovery" method="POST" action="/contact/submit" novalidate>

  {# Trimmed 2026-06-25 (founder): only name + email required; two optional
     conversion fields. Months-behind / QB-version / how-found / AI-recommend
     dropped from VIEW (friction) — lead_source/ai_tool/ai_recommended are now
     AUTO-CAPTURED hidden (see attribution block below). #}
  <div class="intake-grid">
    <div class="intake-field">
      <label class="intake-field__label" for="{{ intakePrefix }}-name">Full name</label>
      <input type="text" id="{{ intakePrefix }}-name" name="name" required autocomplete="name">
    </div>
    <div class="intake-field">
      <label class="intake-field__label" for="{{ intakePrefix }}-email">Work email</label>
      <input type="email" id="{{ intakePrefix }}-email" name="email" required autocomplete="email">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="intake-field">
    <label class="intake-field__label" for="{{ intakePrefix }}-convincing-page">Which page convinced you? <span class="intake-field__optional">optional</span></label>
    <input type="text" id="{{ intakePrefix }}-convincing-page" name="convincing_page" autocomplete="off" placeholder="e.g. the cleanup page, a city page, the cost page">
  </div>

  <div class="intake-field">
    <label class="intake-field__label" for="{{ intakePrefix }}-message">Anything specific? <span class="intake-field__optional">optional</span></label>
    <textarea id="{{ intakePrefix }}-message" name="message" rows="3" placeholder="A line or two about the state of the file helps us scope the call."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="intake-consent">
    <label class="intake-checkbox"><input type="checkbox" name="consent" value="agreed" required><span>{{ intakeConsent or "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this inquiry." }}<span class="intake-checkbox__help">We&rsquo;ll only use your details to respond to this request. See our <a href="/legal/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a>.</span></span></label>
  </div>

  {# Hidden metadata — names + data-meta identical to the locked contract.
     URL params override these defaults; empty params never wipe (round-6 engine). #}
  <input type="hidden" name="intent"       data-meta="intent"       value="{{ intakeIntent }}">
  <input type="hidden" name="source_page"  data-meta="source_page"  value="{{ page.url }}">
  <input type="hidden" name="source_type"  data-meta="source_type"  value="{{ intakeSourceType }}">
  <input type="hidden" name="funnel_stage" data-meta="funnel_stage" value="{{ intakeFunnelStage }}">
  <input type="hidden" name="referring_page" id="{{ intakePrefix }}-referring-page" value="" data-referrer-tracker>

  {# AI-attribution + lead source — AUTO-CAPTURED (hidden), never asked.
     tb-forms.js deriveAttribution() fills these from ?lead_source=/?ai_tool=
     URL params + the referrer (a visit from chatgpt.com/claude.ai/perplexity.ai
     → lead_source=ai-assistant + the tool + ai_recommended=yes; google/bing →
     search; another site → referral). collect() still sends all keys. #}
  <input type="hidden" name="lead_source"    value="" data-attr-source>
  <input type="hidden" name="ai_tool"        value="" data-attr-aitool>
  <input type="hidden" name="ai_recommended" value="" data-attr-airec>

  {# Honeypot — bots fill it; humans never see it. NOT in the payload. #}
  <div class="sr-only" aria-hidden="true">
    <label for="{{ intakePrefix }}-company-website">Company website (leave blank)</label>
    <input type="text" id="{{ intakePrefix }}-company-website" name="company_website" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">
  </div>

  <div>
    <button class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" type="submit" data-cta="contact-form-submit">{{ intakeSubmit or "Send the Discovery Brief" }}</button>
    <p class="intake-form__reassurance">{{ intakeReassurance or "Same business day · no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." }}</p>
  </div>
</form>
